<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>On the page describing it's use (<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.db.table.relationships.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a>) the first arguement to findDependentRowset is described as either the dependent table's model or the string of the model. There is an important difference.</p>

<p>Where the dependent table is held in another database, you must pass in an instance of the model.</p>

<p>When passed in as a string, findDependentRowset assumes the database is that of the row.</p>

